description:
A small rosary used to ward off evil. Though its power
is weak, it is better than nothing.
name: Rosary Beads

description:
An old, rusted mask covering one's mouth. Said to be
the symbol of the Judges, who speak no evil.
name: Judge's Mask

description:
Clothes you were found wearing. Heavily worn, they 
offer little protection.
name: Judge's Robes

description:
A ring gifted to the Judges, to signify that they are 
chosen by God.
name: Judge's Ring

description:
Though worn by an Angel, this item was crafted by 
human hands. Provides much warmth.
name: Knit Scarf

description:
A uniform indicating enrollment in the Angel Corps.
Signifies an Angel yet to have completed training.
name: Cadet Uniform

description:
The ultimate symbol of Angelicness. 
Doesn't appear to come off.
name: Halo

description:
Uniform for a student. Has little protective use, 
but looks stylish.
name: School Uniform

description:
A small amulet bearing the Bergen family crest. 
One can feel a sense of familial pride from it.
name: Bergen Crest

description:
Fanciful robes of a priestess. Denotes high status
and wealth.
name: Priestess Robes

description: A decorative bow, beloved by young girls.
name: Gothic Bow

description:
A souveneir shirt. Offers little protection,
but is apparently popular.
name: "I Heart Kryma" Shirt

description:
Goggles designed to increase one's Faith by 
blocking out lustful sights. Greatly reduces accuracy.
name: See No Evil

description:
Helmet designed to block out sinful words. Resists 
sinful statuses, at the cost of evasion.
name: Hear No Evil

description:
Greatly increases one's Prayer Point growth, 
at the cost of all other stats.
name: Think No Evil

description:
The robes of the Kryma Church, who act as leaders and
guardians of the town.
name: Kryma Church Robes

description:
A finely made cross necklace, sold only in Kryma. 
Carried by almost everyone in the Western Sector.
name: Bronze Cross Necklace

description:
Due to its high price, this silver cross necklace is 
worn primarily in the Eastern Sector of Kryma.
name: Silver Cross Necklace

description:
Reserved for only the elite of the elite, few in Kryma
can afford this powerful luxury.
name: Golden Jeweled Rosary

description:
A necklace cobbled together from junk. Does it even
work?
name: Cheap Cross Necklace

description:
Blessed helm created to withstand a Beasts' attack. 
Only the bravest of Priests donned it.
name: Church Helmet

description:
On top of their ordinary duties, Kryma Priests would 
don this armor when banishing Beasts.
name: Church Armor

description:
Those in the slums could not afford protection from the
Beasts, so faced them with only their average clothes.
name: Slum Hunter Jacket

description:
Beast Hunters often kept small bibles to boost their
faith while performing their duties.
name: Pocket Bible

description:
A magnificent many-colored coat, guaranteed to make one
stand out on the battlefield. Beasts seem to love it.
name: Many Colored Coat

description:
One of 3 pieces of the Armor of God. The Breastplate of
Righteousness allows one to retain their Prayer Points.
name: Breastplate of Righteous

description:
One of 3 pieces of the Armor of God. The Belt of Truth
grants great resistance to all illness and ailments.
name: Belt of Truth

description:
One of 3 pieces of the Armor of God. The Shield of 
Faith slowly replenishes one's Faith in battle.
name: Shield of Faith
